WEBVTT

00:01.182 --> 00:02.626
<i>Previously on Fringe...</i>

00:02.661 --> 00:04.320
When you asked me
to come back to this world

00:04.404 --> 00:06.322
- with you, you said...
- That you belonged with me.

00:06.390 --> 00:08.391
And so I came back for you.

00:08.492 --> 00:09.909
And we started
seeing each other.

00:09.993 --> 00:11.444
I thought she was you, Olivia.

00:14.114 --> 00:15.531
I'm sorry.

00:15.599 --> 00:17.616
Olivia was never treated
with Cortexiphan.

00:17.667 --> 00:19.118
I might have been.

00:19.202 --> 00:20.586
Walter, what did you do to us?

00:20.653 --> 00:24.190
We believed that
our world needed guardians.

00:24.257 --> 00:26.192
And that you children
would be those protectors.

00:26.259 --> 00:28.127
I'm sorry.

00:28.228 --> 00:30.546
- <i>The First People</i>.
- By Seamus Wiles.

00:30.630 --> 00:32.198
"They made
the ultimate discovery.

00:32.265 --> 00:34.533
"A mechanism containing
both the power

00:34.601 --> 00:36.469
to create and to destroy."

00:36.520 --> 00:37.853
This machine is dangerous.

00:37.921 --> 00:39.238
When we put the
word out that we were looking

00:39.339 --> 00:40.973
for copies of the book,
we found out

00:41.024 --> 00:42.041
we weren't the only ones.

00:42.109 --> 00:44.343
- Who?
- William Bell.

