01:19.146 --> 01:21.147
Hmm.

01:36.446 --> 01:38.114
Hmm.

02:03.056 --> 02:05.057
Hmm.

02:27.914 --> 02:30.749
<i>The First People</i>.

02:30.800 --> 02:32.918
You and your secrets.

02:41.928 --> 02:45.147
Yes, call Agent Dunham, please.

02:45.232 --> 02:47.082
So they all say
essentially the same thing.

02:47.150 --> 02:49.018
Not essentially.
Precisely.

02:49.085 --> 02:51.403
Despite being attributed
to different authors.

02:51.471 --> 02:54.273
A fantastical idea
and I have yet to uncover

02:54.324 --> 02:56.358
why William was pursuing it.

02:56.443 --> 02:57.860
That being said,

02:57.944 --> 02:59.161
it was information in the books

02:59.246 --> 03:00.829
that lead us directly
to the coordinates

03:00.914 --> 03:02.648
where we recovered
the pieces of the device.

03:02.699 --> 03:05.284
Which makes them impossible
discount.

03:07.587 --> 03:08.987
I've been thinking
about the journal

03:09.089 --> 03:11.457
the other Olivia wrote
while she was here.

03:11.508 --> 03:13.459
Perhaps her writing might
shed some light.

03:13.510 --> 03:15.844
Uh, no. I read her file
and she didn't mention

03:15.929 --> 03:17.379
<i>The First People</i> or the device.

03:17.464 --> 03:21.016
Oh, I hadn't realized.

03:21.101 --> 03:24.637
I... imagine that must
have been awkward,

03:24.688 --> 03:27.573
reading her account
of her time with Peter.

03:27.641 --> 03:29.692
Though it seems
somewhere along the way

03:29.776 --> 03:31.977
she did start to develop
genuine feelings for him.

03:32.028 --> 03:33.696
I see.

03:33.780 --> 03:35.397
And did that surprise you?

03:35.482 --> 03:37.399
No.

03:37.484 --> 03:39.368
I mean, I understand
how that could happen.

03:42.093 --> 03:43.236
But...

03:43.356 --> 03:45.457
But what?

03:45.525 --> 03:51.046
Just makes me wonder
if maybe he feels the me way.

03:51.131 --> 03:54.333
And I would understand if he did.

03:54.384 --> 03:59.138
I... I was her
for while and she's...

03:59.205 --> 04:02.591
She's like me, but better.

04:02.659 --> 04:03.875
Oh, Olivia...

04:03.927 --> 04:05.427
No, I mean,
she still has her mother

04:05.512 --> 04:08.880
and she wasn't
experimented on as a child.

04:08.932 --> 04:10.882
And she can laugh.
She has real friends.

04:10.934 --> 04:13.235
She even wears a dress
every once in a while.

04:13.270 --> 04:15.053
Yes, but even so,

04:15.105 --> 04:19.325
you don't know
what Peter's thinking.

04:19.392 --> 04:22.311
William and I...

04:22.395 --> 04:25.497
We also had
a complicated relationship.

04:25.565 --> 04:27.149
If there's one thing I regret,

04:27.217 --> 04:28.951
it's that we never
honestly acknowledged

04:29.002 --> 04:31.337
how we felt about each other.

04:31.404 --> 04:34.173
Don't make the same mistake
that I did.

04:34.257 --> 04:37.676
If you want to know
how Peter feels...

04:37.744 --> 04:39.745
Ask him.

04:44.801 --> 04:46.185
Ah.

04:46.252 --> 04:48.220
What is it?

04:48.271 --> 04:50.589
Ooh!

04:50.640 --> 04:52.107
Hey, now you can finally
get the real answers

04:52.192 --> 04:53.525
to the mysteries
of the universe, Warren.

04:53.593 --> 04:55.694
Yeah.

04:55.762 --> 05:01.317
Tell me, oh eight-ball,
will we get the Fowler Grant?

05:01.401 --> 05:04.286
Oh.
"Outlook not so good."

05:04.321 --> 05:06.071
Thank you.

05:06.122 --> 05:09.491
♪ Happy birthday to you, ♪

05:09.609 --> 05:13.495
♪ happy birthday to you, ♪

05:13.613 --> 05:18.334
♪ happy birthday dear Warren, ♪

05:18.418 --> 05:22.338
♪ happy birthday to you. ♪

05:24.224 --> 05:25.574
Make a wish, Warren.

05:25.642 --> 05:28.510
I wish I never
hear you guys sing again.

05:33.299 --> 05:35.901
- You're very popular today.
- Oh, yeah, once a year.

05:35.968 --> 05:38.970
Thanks, Grace.

06:07.166 --> 06:09.134
Gaah! Ah!

06:13.139 --> 06:14.940
Warren?

06:17.694 --> 06:20.729
Ah! Ah!

